%F A025581 As a sequence: a(n) = (((trinv(n)-1)*(((1/2)*trinv(n))+1))-n), with trinv(n) = floor((1+sqrt(1+8*n))/2). Cf. A002262.
%F A025581 a(n) = A004736(n+1) - 1.
%F A025581 G.f. for T(n,k): y / ((1-x)^2 * (1-x*y)). - _Ralf Stephan_, Jan 25 2005
%F A025581 For the cubic equation satisfied by T(n, k) see the comment on a problem by Viète above. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, May 12 2015
%F A025581 G.f. for a(n): -(1-x)^(-2) + (1-x)^(-1) * Sum_{n>=0} (n+1)*x^(n*(n+1)/2). The sum is related to Jacobi theta functions. - _Robert Israel_, May 12 2015
%F A025581 T(n, k) = sqrt((4*A105125(n, k) - A051162(n, k)^3)/(3*A051162(n, k))). See a comment above. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, May 15 2015
%F A025581 a(n) = (1/2)*(t^2 + t - 2*n - 2), where t = floor(sqrt(2*n+1) + 1/2) = round(sqrt(2*n+1)). - _Ridouane Oudra_, Dec 01 2019
%F A025581 a(n) = ((1/2) * ceiling((-1 + sqrt(9 + 8 * n))/2) * ceiling((1 + sqrt(9 + 8 * n))/2)) - n - 1. - _Ryan Jean_, Apr 22 2022
